                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="13739571" author="jukkaz" created="Wed, 14 Aug 2013 11:55:35 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hmm, it looks like the best way to avoid that deadlock is to have the NodeStore push out events to the ChangeDispatcher, instead of it pulling them. That way there&apos;s no synchronization loop to worry about.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13752477" author="mduerig" created="Wed, 28 Aug 2013 15:03:31 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I committed an initial fix for this at revision 1518226. In contrast to Jukka&apos;s suggestion I still pull the changes. But instead of locking I try to acquire the lock and if that fails just do nothing. This is not a problem since any missed changes will be picked up in the next run. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13753420" author="mduerig" created="Thu, 29 Aug 2013 08:23:23 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Turns out that my previous fix only does half of the story. A dead lock can still occur when the lock are acquired the other way around.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13754483" author="mduerig" created="Fri, 30 Aug 2013 08:11:32 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;There is a much simpler solution: just take the offending statement out of the lock. See revision 1518906&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13754484" author="mduerig" created="Fri, 30 Aug 2013 08:11:49 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Fixed at revision 1518906&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13772753" author="alex.parvulescu" created="Fri, 20 Sep 2013 07:01:35 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Bulk close for the 0.9 release&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
